1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,040
Want to make your accessibility statement page easier for your customers to find?

2
00:00:05,040 --> 00:00:11,540
In this video, I'll show you exactly how to add a page to your Shopify menu,

3
00:00:11,540 --> 00:00:13,670
so your customers can access it effortlessly.

4
00:00:13,670 --> 00:00:17,450
If you're new to Shopify or just getting started,

5
00:00:17,450 --> 00:00:19,000
don't worry, I'll walk you through each step clearly.

6
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:23,170
By the end of this video, you'll know how to link any page to your store's navigation,

7
00:00:23,610 --> 00:00:25,750
making browsing intuitive for everyone.

8
00:00:25,750 --> 00:00:27,080
Step 1.

9
00:00:27,080 --> 00:00:30,680
From your Shopify dashboard, click on Content,

10
00:00:30,680 --> 00:00:32,040
then select Menus.

11
00:00:32,040 --> 00:00:33,960
This is where you manage all your store's menus.

12
00:00:33,960 --> 00:00:35,210
Step 2.

13
00:00:35,210 --> 00:00:36,790
Choose the menu you want to edit.

14
00:00:36,790 --> 00:00:41,200
For this video, we'll use the footer menu, which appears at the bottom of your store.

15
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:43,400
Click on it to see the existing menu items.

16
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:44,520
Step 3.

17
00:00:44,520 --> 00:00:46,050
Click on Add menu item.

18
00:00:46,050 --> 00:00:50,000
Enter the name of the new item, for example, Accessibility statement.

19
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:52,650
Step 4, link this menu item to the page you want it to lead to.

20
00:00:52,650 --> 00:00:56,660
Since this is an accessibility statement, select your accessibility statement page.

21
00:00:56,660 --> 00:00:57,800
Step 5.

22
00:00:57,800 --> 00:00:59,420
Click save to update the menu.

23
00:00:59,420 --> 00:01:00,810
Step 6.

24
00:01:00,810 --> 00:01:03,050
Go to your online store and click up here to view your store.

25
00:01:03,050 --> 00:01:12,600
You'll see the accessibility statement page successfully added to your footer menu, ready for your customers to access easily.

26
00:01:12,600 --> 00:01:16,920
Now your Shopify menu is updated and your customers can navigate your store more easily.

27
00:01:16,920 --> 00:01:23,300
Don't forget to try it yourself and make your store even more user friendly.